<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Since the 1.52 patch, it seems many of sorcerors are content to be playing, through respec, the role of a mini-wizard, or wind-theurg wanna-be..whatever you may want to call it.<P>Personally, I chose to play a sorceror because I wanted to play the main crowd-controler of Albion. CC was by far the most rewarding experience I got out of the game. Only fellow sorcerors know the exhilatating feeling of controling the flow of the battle, and often the outcome of it.<P>As of now, a main CC'er of Albion, Sorcerors are hardly on par with their counterparts - bards of Hibernia, and healer of Midgard. <P>Main reason behind our inadequacy is our survivability. Another one is our lack of Insta-CC spells. Alot of us knows the detail behind these, so I won't delve into it.<P>I believe, to make sorceror viable as the main CC'er of Albion and make them competitive against other CC'ers, vast improvement of Mind spec line has to be made. This *buffing* of sorceror must be done to help Mind-spec sorcerors only, and not to overpower Body-spec sorcerors.<P>Proposed improvements to Mind Spec-line:<P>*the examples are given as general idea*<P>A. Add Constitution self-buff.<BR>ex.) 23 mind spec = 20 con , 33 mind spec, = 40 con, 43mind spec = 80 con<P>B. Add upgraded armor absorption self-buff (does not stack with our baseline abs. buff)<BR>ex.) 30 mind spec = 14%abs buff, 40mind spec = 19%abs buff<P>C. Add Armor Factor self-buff (stacks with our baseline af buff)<BR>ex.) 33 mind spec = 75 af buff, 43mind spec = 150 af buff<P>D. Add Insta-mezz to mind-spec, make it so only the highest mind spec'd sorc can get the aoe versions<BR>(same timer & radius as bard/healer's versions)<BR>ex.) 28mind = single target insta-mezz, 38mind = aoe insta mezz, 48mind = aoe insta mezz<P>E. make all aoe-mezz radius 350, same as bard and healer.<P>***Give Healers and Bard ability to QC their mesmerize spells only.<P><BR>So, let's hear it from fellow sorcerors/ess. Any opinions, ideas, criticisms are all welcomed, as long as they're constructive.<BR> <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Let's hope Mind-spec'd sorcerors become viable once again.<P>--------------------<P>Jinju<BR>Sorceress Prime<BR>The Knights Eternal of Tristan
</FONT>
