<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>A. Add Constitution self-buff.<BR>ex.) 23 mind spec = 20 con , 33 mind spec, = 40 con, 43mind spec = 80 con<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I'm not so sure about this one.  First off, with our HP-table, we wont actually get squat for HPs out of this.  Plus, there are clerics that can buff us with con...this would NOT stack with the cleric buff.  And can you imagine the screams from other classes at giving us an 80con buff (even though we would get fewer HPs from it than a tank would get from a 40pt buff).<P>Instead, I would vote for BASELINE acuity buff.  Acuity (Int/Cha/Pie/Emp/etc) is the only line that does not have a baseline buff, and most clerics are not high enough to give you a decent specline acuity buff anyway.  I have an Avalonian with maxed Int, Acuity 2, and a cleric who has the highest acuity buff AND mastery of arcane 2 (6% increase to buffs).  I still can only hit 290 Intelligence.  Yet my melee counterparts can easily get attributes well into the 300's with only modertate buffing.<P>--------------------<P><B>Quote 7/2/02 - i3ullseye, Sorcerer Team Lead: Actually no, i am not 'your' representative. this has been stated before. many TLs do not post ANYWHERE except the pendragn boards. Noone has to try to get ANY feedback from the general populace.</B><P><B>**********************</B><P>Palomides / Alat-Seldi<BR>Mezmo - Level 50.1 Sorcerer<BR>Tagalong - Level 43 Enhance Cleric<BR>Siege - Level 33 Armsman<BR>Terrenus - Level 28 Earth Wizard<BR>Miracle - Level 11 Rejuv Cleric<BR>Recurve - Level 10 Scout
